                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, careless</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (strong red, strong vermillion)</seg>
                        Scribe: ʿƎnqʷä Śǝllāse; Gabra
                           ʾIyasus. The scribe, ʿƎnqʷä Śǝllāse, is mentioned in the
                        supplication formula on <locus target="#39va">39va</locus> ls. 6-7, 45vb
                        l.11. 
 Gabra ʾIyasus is a secondary scribe who wrote (in strong
                        vermillion) the names of the months in the upper margins and names of the
                        secondary donors. He is mentioned in the supplication formulas on <locus target="#13rb">13rb</locus> and 16ra.<date>19th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the protagonist; names of the
                           donors and the scribe; a few lines on the incipit page of Text I; 1st and
                           2nd lines of the incipit of Texts II-IV; the initial line of Text V; one
                           or two initial lines of the sections of Texts I, II, III; names of the
                           months; elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals or their
                           elements. 
 Names of the months and names of the secondary donors are
                           rubricated in strong vermillion.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
