               <provenance>The original donors are mentioned in the
                     supplication formulas throughout the Ms.: Walda Śǝllāse (e.g., 3rb, 10vb, 13rb, 14rb, 30ra), his father Walda ʿAbiyä
                     ʾƎgziʾ (e.g., 62ra, 74rb), his mother Walatta
                     Hāymānot (e.g., 6vb, 10vb, 14rb), his wife Walatta
                     Madḫǝn (e.g., 13rb, 14rb, 22ra, 30ra), Zärʿa
                     Yoḥannǝs (e.g., 59vb). Also, they are mentioned
                     in the concluding supplication on 76ra. 
                     
 Other names have been written later over the names of the original
                     donors: Walda Rufāʾel (e.g., 3rb, 10vb, 13va),
                     Walatta Śǝllāse (e.g., 6vb, 13rb), Gabra Mikāʾel
                     (e.g., 11ra), Gabra ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer (20ra), Walatta Ḥǝywat (e.g., 20ra), Walda Kidān (e.g., 23vb),
                     Walatta Krǝstos (e.g., 24ra). They are rubricated
                     in strong vermilion.</provenance></history>
